### CloudPe CMP API — VS Code REST Client
### Extension: humao.rest-client
### Extension Docs: https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client
###
### API Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs
###

### Values are read from .env in this folder via {{$dotenv VAR}}.
###
### -------------------- sample .env (copy to ./.env) --------------------
### # --- Step 1: fill these before running authenticate ---
### hostname=app.cloudpe.com
### apiKey=your_api_key
###
### # --- Step 2: fill after listFlavors / listImages / listNetworks / listVolumeTypes ---
### regionId=bde56e52-6dfa-4a35-b729-dae711c69e36
### projectId=14ec923c-9a36-450e-9c69-38ed3f65c775
### flavorId=d1c3ef2b-236c-4900-8c32-3bfb25242ad3
### imageId=23e94221-e4b3-42ca-b209-ce19f5e33a58
### volumeType=Eco NVMe
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------

# Fill in the variables below, then click "Send Request" above any ###

@baseUrl = https://{{$dotenv hostname}}/api/v1
@apiKey  = {{$dotenv apiKey}}
###

# List all regions
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/list_regions_api_v1_regions_get
GET {{baseUrl}}/regions
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

@regionId  = {{$dotenv regionId}}

###

# List projects for a specific region
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/list_projects_api_v1_projects_get
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects?region_id={{regionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

###

# List flavors for a specific region
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/list_flavors_api_v1_flavors_get
GET {{baseUrl}}/flavors?region_id={{regionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

###

# List images for a specific region
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/list_images_api_v1_images_get
GET {{baseUrl}}/images?region_id={{regionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

###

# List volume types (storage policies) for a specific region.
# Use the returned `name` (or `vhi_name`) as `volume.volume_type` in the
# Create instance body — that's what `volumeType` should be set to in .env.
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/list_volume_types_api_v1_volumes_types_get
GET {{baseUrl}}/volumes/types?region={{regionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

###

# Billing cycles — there is no GET endpoint; the v1 create-instance schema
# accepts a fixed enum (app/schemas/v1/instance.py → class BillingCycle).
# Allowed values for the `billing_cycle` field below:
#   - hourly
#   - daily
#   - weekly
#   - monthly
#   - quarterly
#   - semiannually
#   - annually

###

# Create instance
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/create_instance_api_v1_instances_post
# @name createInstance
POST {{baseUrl}}/instances
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "my-api-vm",
  "region_id": "{{regionId}}",
  "project_id": "{{$dotenv projectId}}",
  "flavor_id": "{{$dotenv flavorId}}",
  "image_id": "{{$dotenv imageId}}",
  "volume": {
    "size_gb": 30,
    "volume_type": "{{$dotenv volumeType}}"
  },
  "billing_cycle": "hourly",
  "password": "ChangeMe123!"
}

###

# get instances
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/list_instances_api_v1_instances_get
GET {{baseUrl}}/instances
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

# get instances details
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/get_instance_api_v1_instances__instance_id__get
# instanceId is captured from the previous "Create instance" response.
@instanceId = {{createInstance.response.body.$.id}}
GET {{baseUrl}}/instances/{{instanceId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

# Delete instance
# Docs: https://app.cloudpe.com/api/docs#/v1/delete_instance_api_v1_instances__instance_id__delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/instances/{{instanceId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

###
